  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00109_187618_1666091274292&sectionId=71788&sectionno=41&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00109_187618_1666091274292
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `41. ic95610Continuance of prior rules as to matters for which rules may be made under the Act].---- Rep.`
  line `by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1891 (12 of 1891).`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (71789)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 43
  title `Penalty for breach of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950 for "Chief Court".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00109_187618_1666091274292&sectionId=71789&sectionno=42&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00109_187618_1666091274292
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Whoever breaks any rule made or continued under this Act, not`
  line `being a rule made by the ^1[High Court], shall, on conviction before a Magistrate; be punishable with fine`
  line `which may extend to fifty rupees, or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (71790)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 44
  title `. Repealed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00109_187618_1666091274292&sectionId=71790&sectionno=43&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00109_187618_1666091274292
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `[Power to invest taluqdars with civil jurisdiction].— Rep. by the Oudh Civil Courts Acts, 1879`
  line `(13 of 1879.)`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (71791)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 45
  title `Honorary police-officers`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00109_187618_1666091274292&sectionId=71791&sectionno=44&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00109_187618_1666091274292
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, from time to time, confer on any`
  line `person whom it thinks fit any power which may be exercised by a police-officer under any Act for the`
  line `time being in force, and withdraw any power so conferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
